@startuml
title RWA Tokenized Compliance System - Containers
left to right direction

package "Frontend" {
    component "Next.js Investor\nDashboard" as Dashboard
    component "Next.js Admin\nDashboard" as AdminDashboard
}

package "Backend" {
    component "Java Spring\nCompliance API" as API
    component "KYC AML\nValidator" as Validator
    component "Compliance Rule\nService" as Rules
    component "Asset Offering\nRepository" as Assets
    component "Admin Signer\nSimulation" as Signer
}

package "Blockchain" {
    component "Permissioned\nToken" as Token
    component "Identity\nRegistry" as Registry
}

Dashboard --> API : Submit KYC request,\nlist assets, request lifecycle
AdminDashboard --> API : Approve, reject,\nrevoke, lifecycle,\nassets, rules, audit
API --> Validator : Validate request
API --> Assets : Persist offerings,\nshare classes, positions,\nsubscriptions, redemptions
API --> Rules : Evaluate profiles\nand asset rules
API --> Signer : Approved document hash\nand wallet
Signer --> Registry : addIdentity\ntransaction
Signer --> Token : mint approved\nsubscription tokens
Token --> Registry : Check sender\nand receiver
Registry --> API : Approval events
@enduml